definition: -ly/structural particle: used before a verb or adjective, linking it to preceding modifying adverbial adjunct
certificate/proof/to prove/to demonstrate/to confirm/variant of 症[zheng4]

sentences.english: Certificate of Origin is that phase of the transaction (which is set back to stage Inquiry do).
sentences.chinese: 產地證是在交易的那個階段提供。

sentences.english: Invoice & certificate of origin authenticated by joint foreign(non-arab) chamber of commerce.
sentences.chinese: 由非阿拉伯國外聯合商會認證的發票和產地證。

sentences.english: Certification of Origin application and other issues relevant to customs.
sentences.chinese: 原產地證的申請及其他與海關關務有關的工作。

sentences.english: Certificate of origin to their to do?
sentences.chinese: 產地證是要自己做的嗎？

sentences.english: Certificate issuance of product inspection results and original manufacturers' proof.
sentences.chinese: 九關於產品檢驗發證及產地證明簽發事項。

sentences.english: CO is not required for this Komar regular shipment.
sentences.chinese: 這句話是不需要產地證。

sentences.english: Another thing is to do a general certificate of origin and GSP certificate, we must do.
sentences.chinese: 再就是做一般產地證的和普惠制證書的，也要去做。

sentences.english: We enclose packing lists, bill of lading, invoice, certificate of origin and import licence.
sentences.chinese: 寄上包裝單，提貨單，發票，產地證和進口許可證。
